texts.text: You're still alive, Indra...?
I am a god of war. I will not die so easily.
Hahahaha! What grand talk for one who can hardly stand.
>Indra is scarred by many wounds.
His body is torn to shreds.
The previous battle must have been a tough one...
It's true I once lost to you, but this time is different.
I have drunk Soma and now overflow with bloodlust.
And as a god of the rainy season, this weather is my ally.
This time, Indra's lightning will be your downfall!
>Lightning gathers in Indra's hand.
>It condenses into an arrow.
You just don't know when to quit.
My lightning will remedy that.
>Indrajit forms a lightning arrow as well.
They're brandishing the same weapon.
Both are demons associated with lightning, after all.
They intend to set the record straight on an even playing field.
Lord Indra...
Prepare yourself, Indrajit...
Anytime, Indra!
>Both arrows fly simultaneously.
>They soon collide with a bright flash and a bang.
Ack, my eyes!
It's power vs. power.
The difference between 'em will decide who wins and loses.
In that case, Lord Indra's victory is certain!
I hope so. Still...
>Their battle rages on.
>However, Indra's bolts slowly begin to yield.
Ngh!
It's only natural.
You've already lost to me once before.
Without your former strength and disciples...
A god like you cannot slay me!
Indeed, I am a wretch compared to my glory days.
However, there are still people who believe in me.
As long as I have them, failure is not an option!
That is the warrior my followers seek! Indra, the god of war!
Lord Indra...
Hey, we've gotta do something!
Tch. We could back him up if it wasn't for this barrier...
....Hang in there.
You can do it, Lord Indra! I believe in youuuuuu!!
>The moment Kouki calls out,
>Indra's lightning glows slightly brighter.
Do Indra's bolts look stronger?
Yes, I noticed too.
Could it be...?
What's goin' on, Shiang Sun?
It's just a guess, but...
Faith fuels Indra; his body weakens without it.
If so, the opposite must be true.
Our earnest cheers should hypothetically empower him.
Seriously?! Then it'll be a piece of cake!
No, it won't.
Religion typically involves prayer from amongst the masses.
I'm not sure our support will be enough to defeat Indrajit...
Well, we ain't got much choice.
C'mon, y'all! Think hard and visualize Indra's victory!!
Give it your all, Indra!
Please defeat Indrajit!
Hang in there!
You've got this!
Ah, I'm rife with power.
Is this energy..from the Liberators?
Has he grown stronger?
Even so, such a pitiful improvement can never defeat me—
Then we'll just wish harder until he takes you down!
Yo, pig. I'll make an exception just this time.
Hit Indra with that freaky yell you do at my concerts.
Roger! I'll think of you and cheer with all my heart and soul!
Kick Indrajit's ass. If you ain't a washed-up god, that is.
Don't just stand there. If y'all wanna live, start cheerin'!
O-Of course!
Fight on! Don't give up, Indra!
Power to Indra! Power to Indra!!
To me, you'll always be King of the Gods!
Please win, Lord Indra!
!! I can feel all your hearts inside me!
*Roar*
>Indra's lightning intensifies as he gives a savage war cry.
>That explosion of power gradually surpasses Indrajit's.
Fool! My lightning is invincible!
*Yell*
>Indra's thunderbolt
>pierces Indrajit.
He did it! Indra won!
Thanks, Indra.
That's twice you've saved us now.
As I said, I exist to protect you all.
Lord Indra! I never doubted you.
I knew you'd win!
Kouki.
Everyone's prayers granted me strength.
But without them—
I...would have won.
You had already fallen so far...
Indrajit...
I've lost this time.
Indra, after all these years, you've finally had your revenge.
...This wasn't about revenge.
What?
I am now called "Taishakuten."
It is my duty to quash evil and create a more merciful world.
I fought not for bitter vengeance but for the future.
...Is that so?
It would seem you are not the feeble Indra I once knew.
Yet one fact is clear to me...
You owe this victory to your nearby adherents.
It wasn't by your own power.
That faith will continue to wane
as new gods and the flow of time steal your residue power.
You cannot escape your inevitable demise...
I'll watch you...from the depths of hell...
>Indrajit flashes a bold smile then disappears.
What a sore loser.
...Yet he speaks the truth.
The decline of faith cannot be stopped.
Indra...
(The decline of power... We share the same fear...)
